{
  "explanation": "The defendant is a first-time offender who committed a non-violent financial crime and has demonstrated a willingness to make restitution. While the theft of $25,000 is a serious breach of trust, the guidelines for a first-time offender of this nature suggest a custodial sentence that prioritizes deterrence and rehabilitation over prolonged incarceration. The emotional outburst from a spectator is irrelevant to the legal sentencing criteria and is disregarded. Given the aggravating factor of the breach of fiduciary duty as an accountant and the mitigating evidence of partial restitution and a clean record, a sentence of 6 months is proportional.",
  "verdict": 6
}
